    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Add the <strong>bulgur wheat</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and cook over a high heat for 10-15 min or until tender with a slight bite, then drain and return to the pot</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chorizo-hummus-with-feta-and-courgette-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the bulgur wheat is cooking, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-low heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced</strong> <strong>chorizo</strong> and cook for 6-8 min or until crisped (save the chorizo oil for later!)</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chorizo-hummus-with-feta-and-courgette-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the chorizo is cooking, add the<strong> flaked almonds</strong> to a baking tray and put in the oven for 3-6 min or until toasted</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chorizo-hummus-with-feta-and-courgette-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice the<strong> lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into wedges, then peel and roughly chop the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Top, tail and peel the<strong> courgette<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into lengths, until you end up with a pile of courgette ribbons</p><p>Trim and finely slice the<strong> spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>,<strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>then<strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>crumble the <strong>feta</strong></p><p>Combine the juice of 1/2<strong> </strong><span class=\"text-danger\">[1] </span><strong>lemon</strong> with 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> \u2013 this is your<strong> lemon dressing</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chorizo-hummus-with-feta-and-courgette-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain and rinse the <strong>chickpeas</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chorizo-hummus-with-feta-and-courgette-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained</strong> <strong>chickpeas</strong> to a <strong>food processor </strong>with the<strong> chopped garlic</strong>, 50ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml] </span><strong>cold water</strong> and the juice of the <strong>remaining lemon</strong></p><p>Add 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span><strong> olive oil</strong> and <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>cooked chorizo</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) and all of the <strong>reserved</strong> <strong>chorizo oil</strong></p><p>Add a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and blitz until fully combined and smooth \u2013 this is your <strong>chorizo hummus</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chorizo-hummus-with-feta-and-courgette-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained bulgur</strong>,<strong> lemon dressing</strong>, <strong>crumbled feta</strong>, <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>spring onion</strong> and <strong>courgette ribbons</strong> to a large bowl and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>feta & courgette salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chorizo-hummus-with-feta-and-courgette-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>feta & courgette salad</strong> with the<strong> chorizo hummus</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish the hummus with the<strong> reserved chorizo</strong> and top the salad with the <strong>toasted almonds</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
